Class GymManager

java.lang.Object
project1.GymManager
public class GymManager extends Object
GymManager is the class that contains the parts that interect with the user. It takes inputs, and print outputs.

    • commandSwitch

      private void commandSwitch(String[] commandToken, MemberDatabase gymMember, FitnessClass[] classList)
      Response to given comment, activate the method that do the work for it. Similar to the switch.
      Parameters:
      commandToken - Command of the input which is split by " ".
      gymMember - Member list of the gym.
      classList - List of the fitness classes that members can take.

    • addMember

      private static void addMember(String[] commandToken, MemberDatabase gymMember)
      Adding the member to the member list.
      Parameters:
      commandToken - Contains the information of the member to add
      gymMember - The list the member to be added.

    • locationChecker

      private static Location locationChecker(String location)
      Check the location provided is valid. It ignores letter cases.
      Parameters:
      location - the String variable to check.
      Returns:
      the Location object if the String is valid, null if the String in invalid.

    • dobChecker

      private static boolean dobChecker(Date dob)
      Checks if the dob is ok to add to the member. It checks if the dob is valid, if the dob is later than today, and member is the legal age.
      Parameters:
      dob - Date object to check.
      Returns:
      false if the dob is not qualified for the member, true if dob has no problem.

    • nameCaseChanger

      public static String nameCaseChanger(String name)
      Converts the String with capital letter for the first character and small letter for the others.
      Parameters:
      name - String to be converted.
      Returns:
      Converted String.

    • removeMember

      private static void removeMember(String[] commandToken, MemberDatabase gymMember)
      Removes the member from the member list.
      Parameters:

      gymMember - Current list of the member.

    • printFitnessClass

      private static void printFitnessClass(FitnessClass[] classList)
      Print all current fitness classes and members of them.
      Parameters:
      classList - current list of fitness classes.

    • addFitnessClass

      private static void addFitnessClass(String[] commandToken, FitnessClass[] classList, MemberDatabase gymMember)
      Add the member to the fitness class. It checks if member is valid first and add with fitnessAdder method.
      Parameters:
      commandToken - Contains information of the member to add and the class that member would take.
      classList - Current list of the fitness class.
      gymMember - Current member list to check if the member is in the member list.

    • deleteFitnessClass

      private static void deleteFitnessClass(String[] commandToken, FitnessClass[] classList)
      Remove the member from the fitness class. It will check if there is the member in the list first.
      Parameters:
      commandToken - information of the member to be removed.
      classList - Current list of the classes.

    • stringToClass

      private static int stringToClass(String fitClass)
      Changes string of the fitness class to the index of the fitness classes.
      Parameters:
      fitClass - string of the fitness class.
      Returns:
      -1 if string is not valid name, index of the fitness class if there is a class that matches with fitClass.

    • fitnessAdder

      private static void fitnessAdder(Member newFitMember, FitnessClass[] classList, int classNumber)
      Check if the member is already in the class at that time. And add to the class if there is no confliction.
      Parameters:
      newFitMember - Member that will be added to fitness class.
      classList - Current list of the fitness classes.
      classNumber - index of the class that will be added.

    • classChecker

      private static int classChecker(String className, FitnessClass[] classList)
      Changes class name to index of the class list.
      Parameters:
      className - The class name to find.
      classList - List of the fitness classes.
      Returns:
      -1 if className is not found in classList, index of the classList if found.

    • ifExpired

      private static int ifExpired(String expireDate)
      Check the membership is expired or not.
      Parameters:
      expireDate - the date of expiration
      Returns:
      -1 if expired, 0 or 1 if not expired.
